#update method in set -- intersection_update(variables), differnce_update(variable),symmatric_differance_update(variable)
#it simply stored the result in first variable ----
a={'vaibhav',13,"male","hero"}
b={"hi","bye","vaibhav",13}
a.intersection_update(b)
print(a)

a={'vaibhav',13,"male","hero"}
b={"hi","bye","vaibhav",13}
a.difference_update(b)
print(a)

a={'vaibhav',13,"male","hero"}
b={"hi","bye","vaibhav",13}
a.symmetric_difference_update(b)
print(a)

{'male', 'hero'}
{'hi', 'bye', 'male', 'hero'}

#values() -- for printing a values from item.

print(py_dict.items())

dict_values([['vaibhav', 'keshav', 'jon'], [101, 102, 103], ['mumbai', 'pune', 'America'], [1, 2, 3]])
dict_items([('name', ['vaibhav', 'keshav', 'jon']), ('id', [101, 102, 103]), ('city', ['mumbai', 'pune', 'America']), ('sal', [1, 2, 3])])

#stone,paper,sissor game
import random
human_turn=input("choice one (stone, paper, scissor) :")
possible_action=["stone","paper","scissor"]
computer_turn=random.choice(possible_action)
print(f"\nYou chose - {human_turn}, \ncomputer chose - {computer_turn}.\n")
if human_turn == computer_turn:
    print("tie")
elif human_turn =="stone":
    if computer_turn == "scissor":
        print("you win computer loss")
    else:
        ("better next time")
elif human_turn== "paper":
    if computer_turn =="rock":
        print("you win computer loss")
    else:
        print("you loss better next time")
elif human_turn=="scissor":
    if computer_turn =="paper":
        print("you win computer loss")
    else:
        print("you win computer loss")

#operator -- 
''' 1- Arithmatic operator  -- +,-,*,/,//,%,**
    2- comparision operator -- <,>,<=,>=,==,!=
    3- logical operator     -- And, or , not
    4- membership operator  -- in , not in
    5- assignment operator  -- +=,-=,*=,/=
    6- identity operator    -- is , not is
    7- bitwise operator     -- & , | (or)
    8- ternary operator     --'''
Out[21]:
' 1- Arithmatic operator  -- +,-,*,/,//,%,**\n    2- comparision operator -- <,>,<=,>=,==,!=\n    3- logical operator     -- And, or , not\n    4- membership operator  -- in , not in\n    5- assignment operator  -- +=,-=,*=,/=\n    6- identity operator    -- is , not is\n    7- bitwise operator     -- & , | (or)\n    8- ternary operator     --'

# Nested if else -- the one condition  id depends on other condition
filename=input("enter filename :")
if filename.endswith(".pdf"):
    if filename.startswith("copper"):
        print(f"processing {filename}")
    elif filename.startswith("iron"):
        print(f"processing {filename}")
    elif filename.startswith("gold"):
        print(f"processing {filename}")
    else:
        print("invalid pdf file name")
else:
    print("please check the file")

#mumbai --> gen --> M --15  F -30
#other --> gen -->  M - 25 F - 35

sal = int(input("Enter the salary:"))
city = input("Enter the city:").lower()
gen = input("Enter the Gen[M/F]:").lower()

if city=='pune':
    if gen=='m':
        bonus = (sal/100)*5
        gross_sal = sal+bonus
        print("Original Sal Before Bonus :",sal)
        print("Bonus:",bonus)
        print("Total Sal:",gross_sal)
    else:
        bonus = (sal/100)*10
        gross_sal = sal+bonus
        print("Original Sal Before Bonus :",sal)
        print("Bonus:",bonus)
        print("Total Sal:",gross_sal)
elif city=='mumbai':
    if gen=='m':
        bonus = (sal/100)*15
        gross_sal = sal+bonus
        print("Original Sal Before Bonus :",sal)
        print("Bonus:",bonus)
        print("Total Sal:",gross_sal)
    else:
        bonus = (sal/100)*30
        gross_sal = sal+bonus
        print("Original Sal Before Bonus :",sal)
        print("Bonus:",bonus)
        print("Total Sal:",gross_sal)
else:
    if gen=='m':
        bonus = (sal/100)*25
        gross_sal = sal+bonus
        print("Original Sal Before Bonus :",sal)
        print("Bonus:",bonus)
        print("Total Sal:",gross_sal)
    else:
        bonus = (sal/100)*35
        gross_sal = sal+bonus
        print("Original Sal Before Bonus :",sal)
        print("Bonus:",bonus)
        print("Total Sal:",gross_sal)

Enter the salary:900000
Enter the city:pune
Enter the Gen[M/F]:M
Original Sal Before Bonus : 900000
Bonus: 45000.0
Total Sal: 945000.0

#print even or odd number from list--
a=[12,23,25,3,4,33,4,56,76,87,89,100,12,32,34,43,50]
even=[]
odd=[]
for i in a:
    if i%2==0:
        even.append(i)
    elif i%2 ==1:
        odd.append(i)
print("even nos :",even)
print("odd nos :",odd)
set(list(even)) # dublicate number will deleted.

even nos : [12, 4, 4, 56, 76, 100, 12, 32, 34, 50]
odd nos : [23, 25, 3, 33, 87, 89, 43]

In [37]:
list=[1,2,33,44,55,34,54,56,76,87,1,2,3,44,56,44,98,78]
unique=[]
duplicate=[]
for i in list:
    if i not in unique:
        unique.append(i)
    else:
        if i in duplicate:
            continue
        else:
            duplicate.append(i)
print(list)
print("unique :",unique)
print("duplicate :",duplicate)
a=unique
b=duplicate
dict(zip(a,b))

[1, 2, 33, 44, 55, 34, 54, 56, 76, 87, 1, 2, 3, 44, 56, 44, 98, 78]
unique : [1, 2, 33, 44, 55, 34, 54, 56, 76, 87, 3, 98, 78]
duplicate : [1, 2, 44, 56]

# fabonaccie series:
def fab():
    a,b=0,1
    while True:
        yield a
        a,b=b,a+b
for i in fab():
    if i<=100:
        print(i)

In [3]:
#factorial
def fact(no):
    i=no
    fact=1
    while i>=1:
        fact=fact*i
        i-=1
    return fact
result=fact(5)
result

120

# Variables types- there are 2 variables types 
# 1- local variables -- used only with in a function only.
# 2- Global variable -- scope in the all function can call any time 
# ex--
a=10          #Global variable
def test1():   
    a=5       #Local variable
    print(a)
def test2():
    c=10
print(a)
test1()      #to call local variable you need to call the function first

# Real Standard Python Code.
''' - Shebang 
    - Doc string
    - import library 
    - Global Section 
    - Global Variable define:
    - def function1():
    - def function2():
    - mainfunction
    - def mainfunction():
    - if__name__=='__main__':
             body            '''

" - Shebang \n    - Doc string\n    - import library \n    - Global Section \n    - Global Variable define:\n    - def function1():\n    - def function2():\n    - mainfunction\n    - def mainfunction():\n    - if__name__=='__main__':\n             body            "

#global keyword :
course="python"
def test():
    print(course)
def a1():
    print(course)
def a2():
    global course    # convert local course into global course - global(variable name)
    course="hadoop"  
    print(course)
print(course)
a2()
print(course)
a1()
print(course)

hadoop
hadoop
hadoop

# Decorator--
def beauty_parlour(fun):
    def makeup():
        print("foundation")
        fun()
        print("finishing touch....")
    return makeup

def normal_girl():
    print("normal girl")
finish = beauty_parlour(normal_girl)
finish()

foundation
normal girl
finishing touch....
In [52]:
# @decorator ---- @fuction call
def decor(fun):
    print("x"*10)
    fun()
    print("x"*10)
@decor
def show():
    print("welcome")

xxxxxxxxxx
welcome
xxxxxxxxxx

def math():

In [58]:
def dbconnection(fun):
    def inner():
        print("welcome to barclays")
        print("checking processing")
        fun()
        print("creating")
        print("fotmate finished")
        print("log out")
    return inner
@dbconnection
def data_dump():
    print("pdf file reading")
    print("table form")
data_dump()

welcome to barclays
checking processing
pdf file reading
table form
creating
fotmate finished
log out

def decor(fun):
    def inner():
        print("#"*3)
        fun()
        print("#"*3)
    return inner
@decor
def show():
    print("hie")
show()

# Types of methods in class
#  1- Instances methods -- its a object opertion instances method -- (self.variable name)
#  2- Class method -- its a operation on a class name -- (cls.variable name)
#  3- Static method -- in that no used of self or cls mrthod it is like local variable
# for changing the the class name  --- @classmethod
# for entering the local variable or static method --- @staticmethod
In [48]:
class product:
    product_company="IBM"
    def __init__(self,prodid,prodname):
        self.id=prodid
        self.name=prodname
    @classmethod                                 # it is for giving new name to company.
    def product_new_cal(cls):
        cls.product_company_new_name="IBM NEW"
    def show(self):
        print("Company name :",product.product_company)
        print("Name of the ID :",self.id)
        print("Name of the Product :",self.name)
        self.product_new_cal()
        print("Company new name :",product.product_company_new_name)
obj=product(101,"vaibhav")
obj.show()

Company name : IBM
Name of the ID : 101
Name of the Product : vaibhav
Company new name : IBM NEW

In [67]:
class product:
    product_company="IBM"
    def __init__(self,prodid,prodname,p,q):
        self.id=prodid
        self.name=prodname
        self.p=p
        self.q=q
    @classmethod                                 # it is for giving new name to company.
    def product_new_cal(cls):
        cls.product_company_new_name="IBM NEW"
    
    @staticmethod
    def addition_num(p,q):
        add_num=p*q
        return add_num
    
    def show(self):
        print("Company name :",product.product_company)
        print("Name of the ID :",self.id)
        print("Name of the Product :",self.name)
        self.product_new_cal()
        print("Company new name :",product.product_company_new_name)
        total=self.addition_num(self.p,self.q)
        print(total)
obj=product(101,"vaibhav",2,3)
obj.show()

Company name : IBM
Name of the ID : 101
Name of the Product : vaibhav
Company new name : IBM NEW

# examples of @staticmethod (multipling number)--
class p:
    def __init__(self,p,q):
        self.p=p
        self.q=q
        
    @staticmethod
    def multi(p,q):
        addnum=p*q
        return addnum
    
    def show(self):
        total=self.multi(self.p,self.q)
        print(total)
o=p(2,10)
o.show()

In [33]:
# examples of @staticmethod (addition of number)--
class v:
    def __init__(self,a,b):
        self.a=a
        self.b=b
    @staticmethod
    def add(a,b):
        total = a+b
        return total
    def show(self):
        result=self.add(self.a,self.b)
        print(result)
z=v(5,5)
z.show()

In [1]:
# Inheritance -- its is known as the get class A properties in class B.
# class A -- parent class , super class , base class
# class B -- child class , sub class , devird class
# There are 5 typics of inheritance
# 1 -- Single inheritance     -- A - B(A)
# 2 -- Multilevel inheritance -- A - B(A) - C(B)
# 3 -- Multipal inheritance   -- A - B - C(A,B)
# 4 -- hybrid inheritance     -- A - B - C - D - E(B,D)
# 5 -- hrican inheritances    -- A - B(A) - C(A) - X(B) - Z(B) - E(C) - F(C)
In [5]:
# 1 -- Single inheritance     -- A - B(A)
class A:
    def m1(self):
        print("in m1")
class B(A):
    def m2(self):
        print("in m2")
obj=B()
obj.m1()
obj.m2()

in m1
in m2
In [9]:
# 2 -- Multilevel inheritance -- A - B(A) - C(B)
class A:
    def m1(self):
        print("in m1")
class B(A):
    def m2(self):
        print("in m2")
class C(B):
    def m3(self):
        print("in m3")
obj=C()
obj.m1()
obj.m2()
obj.m3()
print(C.mro())

in m1
in m2
in m3

    def m1(self):
        super().m1()
        print("instagram id")

    def m1(self):
        super().m1()
        print("facebook id")

class A:
    def m1(self):
        print("in m1 from A")
class B(A):
    def m2(self):
        print("in m1 from B")
class C(B):
    def m3(self):
        print("in m1 from C")
class D(C):
    def m4(self):
        super(B,self).m1()
        print("in m1 from D")
obj=D()
obj.m4()

in m1 from A
in m1 from D

# 1 - Public - with in class outside also accessible.
# 2 - Protected - accessible on parent class and child class only. (_variable).
# 3 - Private - accessible with in class only not access outside of class. (__variable).

# Polymorphism - may functions. - one method having many forms.
# it having 2 types. - 1- overloading.    2- overriding.
# 1- overloading - Same mrthod name but different variable name.
# 2- overriding - same method name but excute will last one only.
# all having 3 types. 
# 1- overloading - 1-operator overloading.  - possible with magic method.
#                  2-Method overloading.    - Not possible.
#                  3-constructor overloading.- Not possible.
## 1- overriding - 1-operator overriding.  - None.
#                  2-Method overriding.    - super().method
#                  3-constructor overriding.- super().method
In [34]:
#magical methods.
# __add__ = addition.
# __sub__ = subtraction.
# __str__ = print statement(print(Obj))
In [44]:
# overloading example - addition 
class Test:
    def __init__(self,val):
        self.val=val
    def __str__(self):
        return "total of obj: {}".format(self.val)
    def __add__(self,other):
        total=self.val+other.val
        return Test(total)
obj_1=Test(2)
obj_2=Test(3)
obj_3=Test(5)
print(obj_1+obj_2+obj_3)

total of obj: 10

In [ ]:
#read-
with open("file_name",'r') as vaibhav:
    vaibhav.read()
    
#write - 
with open("file_name",'w') as vaibhav:
    vaibhav.write("how are you today")
print(vaibhav)

#append -
with open("file_name",'w') as vaibhav:
    data=vaibhav.write("hiee")
print(data)
In [ ]:
# combination of mode:
# 1 - r+ -- read then write.
# 2 - w+ -- write then read.
# 3 - a+ -- append then read.
In [ ]:
# 1 - r+ - read then write.
with open ("file_name",'r+') as fp:
    data= fp.read()
    fp.write("hiee how are you")
print(data)   #it will add old contain + new contain 
# if we clear the old contain used a seek() it will set a pointer.
In [3]:
# seek(n) -- it will set a pointer for where we want to print a data.
#   seek(0) -- pointer will set as 0.
# tell() -- it will say where the pointer is.
In [ ]:
# 2 - w+ - write and read.
with open ("file name",'w+') as fp:
    fp.write("hiee")
    fp.seek(0)        #writen from 0 .
    data=fp.read()
    print(data)
In [ ]:
# 3 - a+ - append then read.
with open("file_name",'a+') as fp:
    fp.write("how are you")
    data=fp.read()
    print(data)

import csv

    w=csv.write(fp)
    w.writerow(["id","sal","mobile"])  # it will print a single line always pass in list.
    w.writerows([[101,25000,+81],[102,30000,+81],[103,35000,+81]]) # for print more lines.

# python functionality of os -- import os -- operating system.
# import os you need to first import this for functionality. -- (directory - folder).
# os.getcwd() -- to check the path of current working dir(folder).
# os.chdir("file_path") -- to change the current dir.
# os.listdir() -- it will give a list of dir(folder) from current dir.
# os.chdir('..')  -- for get one step back from dir.
# os.mkdir('file_name') -- to create a new directory (folder).
# os.rmdir('file_name') -- to remove a dir. (it will removed if the dir is empty).
# (row)/r string -- because of r it will not a consider as a special character.
# os.makedirs(r'm1\m2\m3') -- it will create a multiple dirs whoses name m1 in the m2 in the m3.
# os.removedirs(r'm1\m2\m3') -- it will delete the dirs at a one time.
# os.system("file_name\file_path") -- it is used to access a dir from anywhere.
# import os,shutil -- it is used for strongly delete the dir.
# shutil.rmdir("file_name")

import logging
logging.basicConfig()           #it has defult value level 30 and you can formate it according our used.
logging.critical("critical message")
logging.error("error massage")
logging.warning("warning massage")
logging.info("info massage")
logging.debug("debug massage")
# default it will take 30 level above.

WARNING:root:warning massage

In [ ]:
import logging
# for printing log in file
logging.basicConfig(filename="filename.log")
# for formating massage.
logging.basicConfig(format=%(asctime):%(levelname)s:%(massage)s) # you can formate by your according.
# for formating the date.
logging.basicConfig(datefmt=%d-%m-%Y-%M-%S-%p) #%d-date, %m-month, %Y-year, %M-Minute, %S-second, %P- AM/PM.

# code from log file
import logging

logging.basicConfig(filename='test_l.log',level=10,
                    filemode='w',format='%(asctime)s : %(name)s : %(levelname)s : %(message)s',
                    datefmt='%d - %m - %Y :"time"-: %I - %M - %p')

logger=logging.getLogger('log')       #it assign as a root name
logger.critical("critical massage")
logger.error("error massage")
logger.warning("warning massage")
logger.info("info massage")
logger.debug("debug massage")

import logging

                    filemode='a',format='%(asctime)s : %(name)s : %(levelname)s : %(message)s',
                    datefmt='%d - %m - %Y :"time"-: %I - %M - %p')

logger=logging.getLogger('email')     #it assign as a root name
logger.critical("critical massage")
logger.error("error massage")
logger.warning("warning massage")
logger.info("info massage")
logger.debug("debug massage")

# Git/Git hub - it is a virtual repository which store a file online and for sharing.
# git hub is a central repository where all can access with git bash.
# git hub is a remote repo where developer can pull or push the file by git bash in local repository.
# local repository has 3 compartment -- working dir -- stagging area -- local repo.
# make remote repo in git hub 
# git clone path -- clone in local repo.
# git status -- for checking modification.
# git pull -- get file save in local repo to remote repo.
# git touch file name -- create a file in working dir.
# git add . -- get file in stagging area.
# git commit -m "meassage" -- get file in local repo.
# git push origin head -- upload a file in remote repo in local repo.
In [2]:
# branch -- is used to create a new repo with same file in old repo.
# git checkout branch name -- you can jump into a branch.

# ML - Machine learning.
# machine learning is the Math expression which all thing depends on a math formula.
# Data analysis is act 80% role in data processing.
# 3 types of ML - 1-supervised -- independent target 
#                 2-unsuperised -- clustering algorithm(no target).
#                 3-reinforecment -- self learing algorithm (chess game).
# supervised -- in ML there are 100% data -- 70% data for training --30% data for testing.(predict).
# supervised -- 1-regrations - SLR , MLR 
#               2-classification - LR , DT , RF , XG , KNN
# unsupervised -- k-mean, DB scan.

    'name':['a','b','c','d','e'],
    'city':['mumbai','pune','nashik','pune','usa'],
    'id':[101,102,103,104,105],
    'sal':[11,22,33,44,55]
}

df1= pd.DataFrame({ "city":['pune','mumbai','channai'],
                   "sal_area":['kolkata','new mumbai','gujrat']})

df1['sal_area']=df1['sal_area'].apply(lambda x:x.capitalize())

import re
def clean(s):
    s=re.sub('[A-Za-z]'," ",s)
    return s
df3['country']=df3['country'].apply(clean)

In [132]:
# inner join -- all record will join together.
# left join -- left side all + matched record from right side.
# right join -- right side all + matched record from left side.
# outer join -- matched record + unmatched (all recored).
In [133]:

In [142]:
# left join 
pd.merge(df,df1,on='id',how='left',indicator=True) # all recored from df + matched record from df1
Out[142]:
id name_x name_y _merge
0 101 a A both
1 102 b NaN left_only
2 103 c B both
3 104 d C both
4 105 e NaN left_only
5 106 f D both
In [144]:
#right join
pd.merge(df,df1,on='id',how='right',indicator=True)  # df = matched with with id df1 -- df1= all record.
Out[144]:
id name_x name_y _merge
0 101 a A both
1 103 c B both
2 104 d C both
3 106 f D both
4 600 NaN E right_only
5 900 NaN F right_only
In [146]:
# outer join
pd.merge(df,df1,on='id',how='outer',indicator=True) #all record.
Out[146]:
id name_x name_y _merge
0 101 a A both
1 102 b NaN left_only
2 103 c B both
3 104 d C both
4 105 e NaN left_only
5 106 f D both
6 600 NaN E right_only
7 900 NaN F right_only
In [ ]:
